Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.65,0:00:10.40,Narration Off,,10,10,0,,{\be10}Heiji Hattori, Kazuha Tōyama and Inspector Ōtaki from the Ōsaka Police visited Tōkyō to investigate a case that started in Ōsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.78,0:00:18.99,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran, old man Mouri and I went with them to the crime scene, a room in a flat in Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.33,0:00:24.87,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But we confirmed it was a suicide, and easily closed the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.33,0:00:29.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But as we were waiting for the lift as we left the crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.05,0:00:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speak of the devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.47,0:00:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.51,0:00:42.31,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It looked like a suicide at first glance,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.31,0:00:46.10,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but many things just didn't add up, leading to a murder investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.11,0:00:52.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Following Detective Takagi's questioning, we were able to narrow it down to three suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.74,0:00:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what's your occupation?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.20,0:00:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm an office worker at a building maintenance company.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.99,0:01:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We do stuff like intercoms, delivery lockers and ACs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.04,0:01:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you do lift and security maintenance too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.67,0:01:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, how were you related to the late Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.17,0:01:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your name was in Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mobile phone address book.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.51,0:01:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I was involved in some share trading.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.01,0:01:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then did you make a massive loss on the stock market and have a grudge against Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.85,0:01:29.61,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I-I did have a grudge, but not enough to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.35,0:01:29.61,Signs,,0,0,0,,Isao Mutsu (45)\NBlock Resident
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.40,0:01:37.11,Signs,,0,0,0,,Takurō Yoda (21)\NBlock Resident
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.02,0:01:37.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I lost quite a sum on the stock market on Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s recommendations, but I don't have any bad feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.57,0:01:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's my own fault for not seeing how the shares were going.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.41,0:01:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It stinks of paint thinner in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.33,0:01:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was just adding some colour to the severed head.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.13,0:01:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Severed head?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.84,0:01:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I just made it to look like my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:01:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then if you wanted, you could probably make...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.51,0:02:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...a severed head that looks just like Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.18,0:02:08.77,Signs,,0,0,0,,Naoko Izutsu (32)\NBlock Resident
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:06.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What's your occupation, Izutsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.15,0:02:09.73,Dialogue,,230,0,0,,Can't you see for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.73,0:02:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A tracing stand, screen-tone, a cutter knife, a dip pen, a mapping pen, brushes, Indian ink, and regular ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.90,0:02:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a manga artist! Haven't you ever heard the pen name 'Kotori Misono'?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the manga series with a beautiful female detective Chiba fanboys over?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.54,0:02:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which would suggest you could easily come up with some story
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.54,0:02:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,about how somebody could kill a person in a lift and make it look like he killed himself with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:41.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'd come up with a plot gem like that, I'd write it into my manga!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:46.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The killer is probably the one who hid those things...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.10,0:02:48.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The problem is the trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.05,0:02:53.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How did they kill Fuura{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.09,0:02:59.31,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HAAAA00\t(0,3610,\c)}Seeking comprehensive answers, he clears all mysteries and codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.31,0:03:01.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(0,1790,\c&H88AA00)}A case inside a sealed lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.12,0:03:03.27,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&H88AA00}Hattori and I reveal the shocking trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.27,0:03:04.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&H88AA00)\t(0,1590,\c)}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:06.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(0,2000,\c&HAA00AA)}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.77,0:03:08.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HAA00AA\t(0,1600,\c&H0000FF)\fad(0,500)}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, that Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's taking him so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.19,0:05:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already decided you'll stay over at our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.36,0:05:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, he's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.87,0:05:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how did it go? Did you figure out who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. We heard what the three suspects have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.21,0:05:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they're all a bit suspicious and a bit not...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.21,0:05:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though all three of them could have a potential motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.22,0:05:26.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, the killer's probably that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:28.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The issue is the trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.55,0:05:37.36,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Oh, yeah, apparently there were posters on all lift doors except those on the 2nd and 3rd floors saying 'The lift is undergoing inspection.'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.36,0:05:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. That's how they kept people away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.82,0:05:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was a suicide, you'd think Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would put up those signs so nobody would stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.86,0:05:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.91,0:05:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, if we can't figure it out, shouldn't we try callin' Kudō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.62,0:05:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.38,0:06:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that family restaurant case earlier, he solved the case in a flash when Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} called him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:06.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You moron. He ain't figured anythin' out yet either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, that might not be a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it takes the two of you to do the job of one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on! Who says it takes the two of us—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:20.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Takes two...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:21.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...to do the job of one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.82,0:06:22.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:24.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If this thing was used...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:27.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see! That's why—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.82,0:06:31.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah. Those letters saying 'goodbye'...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.33,0:06:35.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They weren't just a message, disguised as the final words of the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.87,0:06:40.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The killer wrote it because it was necessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:43.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...in order to complete the trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They didn't find any gunshot residue on {\i1}any{\i0} of the three suspects?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.97,0:06:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we've confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.43,0:06:59.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had a report from forensics earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.31,0:07:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for being late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.57,0:07:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Megure, of the Tōkyō Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.23,0:07:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Ōtaki, of the Ōsaka Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologise too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have been sticking my nose into a case in another prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, I heard from Takagi that you've been a great help in the initial investigations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.17,0:07:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, is this really a murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.96,0:07:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw the deceased, Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, shoot himself in the head through the lift window, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.47,0:07:32.76,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Speak of the devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.02,0:07:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.35,0:07:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So isn't it an obvious suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.69,0:07:43.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so at first too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.56,0:07:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the surveillance camera inside the lift was spray-painted using a non-dominant hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.07,0:07:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the watch the deceased was wearing had stopped...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.37,0:07:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That led me to believe something wasn't right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.08,0:08:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those points are indeed rather curious, but you saw the moment when Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.25,0:08:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.71,0:08:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer to your question is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.09,0:08:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer put his gun to Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s head in the lift and said something like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.51,0:08:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'If you don't want to get shot, keep looking out the window.'
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.77,0:08:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then shot him when the lift was passing through this floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.11,0:08:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to those of us who saw it, it really looked like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.24,0:08:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that impossible?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.62,0:08:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless of the circumstances, you'd usually be able to tell, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:49.01,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,If the hand on the side was the killer's hand, the position of the hand holding the gun wouldn't match with Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.01,0:08:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right. If I was the killer, I wouldn't do anything like that. That's a pretty obvious special effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.64,0:08:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if that was the case, wouldn't Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} try to fight back?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe he'd appear calm enough to make it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.06,0:09:06.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are these three the suspects you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.65,0:09:11.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah — they're the residents from these flats without alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.74,0:09:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't just come here for the sake of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.28,0:09:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were called out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.74,0:09:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This kid told us we'd find the truth behind the case if we came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.08,0:09:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. I brought these three here, just like Detective Takagi and Heiji-{\i1}niichan{\i0} told me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where's Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ain't seen him for an hour now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.72,0:09:43.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he was going somewhere with Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.23,0:09:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, they had some business with the shop at the back of this block.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A shop at the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.56,0:09:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A shop at the back...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.98,0:09:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! The back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.57,0:09:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer hid behind Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s back and shot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.62,0:10:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he did that, it'd look more natural than a gun coming from the side, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.54,0:10:09.84,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,If that was the case, then when Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed, his head would've moved from the impact and allowed us to see the killer's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:14.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:17.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! It's Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.85,0:10:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, what are you doing, Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.72,0:10:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! It's Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.64,0:10:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:44.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, what are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.69,0:10:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what we saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.02,0:10:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.98,0:10:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it {\i1}was{\i0} two people standing one behind the other!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.65,0:10:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi and the Ōsakan detective brat just demonstrated it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.07,0:10:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess if you do it well, it looks natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:10:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.54,0:11:04.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry back and explain, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.37,0:11:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.55,0:11:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.26,0:11:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, can we get some explanations?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.93,0:11:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} just told me to stand here and watch everybody's reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.27,0:11:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch our reactions?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.85,0:11:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long have you been there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since a little before the lift came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.86,0:11:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible! We saw you in the lift!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.74,0:11:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's because that was—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Detective Takagi's in the lift again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, this is the truth behind the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.71,0:11:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A tablet PC?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.09,0:11:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I had Detective Takagi borrow this from the electronics shop at the back of the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.93,0:12:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I pressed the tablet against the lift window, and played back the movie I'd made of Detective Takagi's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.19,0:12:10.12,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.40,0:12:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lift windows are divided by the letters saying 'goodbye',
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.45,0:12:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you wouldn't be able to tell it was a tablet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.99,0:12:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, even though it was all my body apart from the head,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.70,0:12:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it really looked as though Detective Takagi was on the lift, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, with the tablet and my body,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.71,0:12:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,two were needed to do the job of one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.59,0:12:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, isn't that impossible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you just pretended to be shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.76,0:12:45.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we saw him shooting himself in the head with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If what you say is right, then while pressing the tablet to the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.10,0:12:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer would have to shoot right in front of his eyes, which is pretty dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.78,0:13:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's no guarantee that the move would work with the footage on the tablet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.16,0:13:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, you ought to be able to find the extra hole from this gunshot in the lift wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.16,0:13:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. We only used one tablet because we didn't have enough time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.13,0:13:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer probably used {\i1}four{\i0} tablets!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.34,0:13:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had four, then you could run footage being sure the movements would match.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.55,0:13:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,F-Four?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.30,0:13:25.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So everything we saw was a video?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.22,0:13:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.56,0:13:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apart from the face, the footage was all of the killer wearing the same suit as Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.73,0:13:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But can you really hold up four tablets in one hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.49,0:13:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer probably stuck the four tablets into a large board.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.03,0:13:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then all they'd have to do is lean the board against the lift doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.37,0:13:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ain't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.41,0:13:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss manga artist who tried to hide the fact that she had four tablets, Naoko Izutsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.34,0:14:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the killer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.10,0:14:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.26,0:14:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anybody who had four tablets could've pulled off that trick just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.69,0:14:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why does that make {\i1}me{\i0} the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.85,0:14:15.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you hid your tablets!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.82,0:14:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That little gizmo on your desk next to the tracing stand — that was a mobile router, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.41,0:14:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Possessing such a thing but not possessing a PC or a tablet of some kind to get on the net is just plain weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.91,0:14:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe my editor left it behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.04,0:14:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm bad with technology, so I don't use a PC.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.42,0:14:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, manga artists are pretty cool, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.42,0:14:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you draw a detective manga series, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.59,0:14:48.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you only have a couple of manga volumes on your shelf!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.43,0:14:53.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's amazing that you can imagine and draw all these kinds of things straight from your head!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.15,0:15:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, if it's a detective manga, then unlike with a fantasy or fairy tale, you need to have some degree of realism.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.32,0:15:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like backgrounds to use as crime scenes, or a weapon like a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.78,0:15:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be impossible to draw that without some kind of resource.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.41,0:15:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Izutsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} {\i1}did{\i0} said she has three assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.33,0:15:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So with a tablet for each assistant and one for her, that makes four.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.59,0:15:27.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how could she take a footage of Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} of him shooting himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.47,0:15:31.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like she could ask him to pretend to be shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.60,0:15:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.98,0:15:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When filming a video like this, just jerk the camera sideways and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.15,0:15:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See! You can make it look like you're being shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.28,0:15:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you wouldn't be able to see a bullet, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.24,0:15:54.25,Dialogue,,10,1,0,,The objects in the background would end up being blurred, but even so, it'd be hard to tell where it is since there's nothing in a lift, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.08,0:15:56.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.37,0:15:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I heard all of this from Heiji-{\i1}niichan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.63,0:16:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Heiji-{\i1}niichan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.34,0:16:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.22,0:16:10.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suddenly I feel like I've become Sleepin' Kogorō...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.35,0:16:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we didn't just happen to be waiting for the lifts at that time, then the trick wouldn't—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.89,0:16:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.56,0:16:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The target was Nanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who goes to the beauty salon at this time every week!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.57,0:16:31.08,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,First, Izutsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} invited Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to a nearby shop, pretendin' she'd like to introduce him to a new client interested in stocks and shares.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.08,0:16:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she said she'd go ahead and wait in front of the lift while askin' him to wear the same suit as the one in the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.79,0:16:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that done, Izutsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who'd arrived first at the lift, sprayed up the security camera,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.30,0:16:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then closed the doors, wrote 'goodbye', and opened them up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.22,0:16:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the inspection notices, nobody was gonna press the button to call it, so the lift stayed where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, you shot Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} dead while he was stunned by the 'goodbye' on the inside of the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.45,0:17:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, you waited around until the time Nanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would go to the beauty salon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.74,0:17:19.04,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Of course, you'd pressed the button on your own floor above the third floor which Nanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} usually got on, and kept the door open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.62,0:17:29.13,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Around the time Nanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would come to the lift, you closed the doors and put up the board with the four tablets against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:37.64,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Then you timed the footage in a way that the scene of Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} puttin' the gun to his head would display as you passed the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:48.03,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,I see. Then all she'd have to do is get off on the floor that her own room is in and get away with the board to make a perfect crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.03,0:17:51.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody can ever create a perfect crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.74,0:17:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see for yourself with all the errors Izutsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.62,0:18:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One was holdin' out your left hand when the police asked to check you for gunpowder residue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.79,0:18:05.25,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Gunpowder residue washes off with water, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.00,0:18:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You held your towel, book and lighter in your right hand, so you're right-handed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.02,0:18:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In line with Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} bein' left-handed, you shot him with your left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.19,0:18:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if you shot him with your right hand, the traces of residue left on the grip wouldn't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.32,0:18:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another pointer was the automatic watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was wearin' a different watch than the one you used in your video,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.70,0:18:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you switched it with the watch he'd given you, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.42,0:18:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to match the times, you shook it a little to make it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.88,0:18:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, those two who wear their watches all the time probably know
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.05,0:18:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that if you only shake the watch just a little, it'll stop pretty quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.51,0:18:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that you didn't know that shows you're the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.64,0:19:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That watch wasn't mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.56,0:19:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The watch I got from Fuura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was for ladies and was a bit slimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.27,0:19:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then whose was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.11,0:19:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Mizuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.03,0:19:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, the old guy who hung himself in this block of flats last month?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.54,0:19:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Sensei'? You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.29,0:19:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was the teacher in charge of my class in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.83,0:19:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I had no idea we lived in the same block until I bumped into him in the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.92,0:19:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this murder was just to get revenge on the man who pushed your mentor to suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.80,0:19:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there's that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.31,0:19:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But mostly, it's just because I got a bit sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.69,0:19:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.94,0:19:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After {\i1}Sensei{\i0} hung himself, I remembered that he still had an album from high school that I'd lent to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.49,0:20:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked the warden to let me into {\i1}Sensei{\i0}'s room, I realised it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.95,0:20:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he'd set up a trick to make it look like he was killed by somebody while he actually committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.09,0:20:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.21,0:20:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was one of my manga, a detective would come up with a deduction and work this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.64,0:20:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in this case, nobody noticed the trick and the whole thing was immediately closed as a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.87,0:20:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I wanted {\i1}Sensei{\i0}'s goal to be achieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.08,0:20:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, as a mystery, it would never have a proper ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.98,0:22:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you'll let me stay over at your place, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.28,0:22:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.44,0:22:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be pretty hard to find a hotel at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.95,0:22:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.91,0:22:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.53,0:22:39.20,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Are you sayin' that you, me, Ōtaki-{\i1}han{\i0} and the kid,\N{\i1}all four of us{\i0} are gonna have to all sleep together in your room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.20,0:22:41.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's gonna be a bit tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.37,0:22:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, how about you come and sleep with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.80,0:22:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.80,0:22:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We could fit Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} between us both like a sandwich! {adaptation because lol river kanji}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.09,0:22:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you two are okay with it, then—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.60,0:22:57.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Watch it, you little pervert.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.81,0:23:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.60,0:23:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello? Ōtaki here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.40,0:23:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Director-general?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.98,0:23:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened for you to call me this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.03,0:23:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A troublesome case just came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.74,0:23:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not really under our jurisdiction, so I was thinking of turning it down,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.54,0:23:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but since you're in Tōkyō right now, I figured I'd ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.87,0:23:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What problematic case?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.88,0:23:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ōtaki, do you believe they really exist in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.05,0:23:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Vampires...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.88,0:23:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you go there for me, do take care...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.10,0:23:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inheritance discussion in question will take place after the evening meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.23,0:23:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't found your boss yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.15,0:23:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. Even though we all split apart to search for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.32,0:24:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A coffin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.36,0:24:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't get inside one of these things before you die!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: 'Heiji Hattori and the Vampire Mansion (One)'!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.25,0:24:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Coffin!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.17,0:24:20.63,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hattori, are you sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.63,0:24:21.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm suckin' blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.96,0:24:23.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah, that's next week.
